>         Mathematics of Surfaces).  

With respect to using PH orientation curves, the sufficient conditions
that Farouki chose for his paper are much easier to solve than the 
nesc. and sufficient conditions given by Dietz, and Farouki is fully 
aware of the Dietz conditions.  I think he chose to use the easier set
because of the extreme messiness involved with solving the full one.  
I think what I did on the full conditions adds little to Farouki's work
besides complication.

 
